{
  "texts": [
    "See Appendix § B.Corollary 4.12 (Separative Strong Frames).",
    "For any full possibility frame F, there is a separative, strong, and full possibility frame (F ≃) □ and a surjective robust possibility morphism from F to (F ≃) □.",
    "Atomic FramesWorld frames and their powerset possibilizations (Examples 2.6 and 2.9) are examples of what we will call atomic possibility frames in Definition 4.14, deviating slightly from the standard definition for posets.",
    "Definition 4.13 (Atomic Poset).",
    "Given a poset ⟨S, ⊑⟩, an atom in ⟨S, ⊑⟩ is an a ∈ S that is not the minimum of ⟨S, ⊑⟩ (if there is one) such that for all x ∈ S, if x ⊑ a, then either x = a or x is the minimum of ⟨S, ⊑⟩."
  ]
}